      {
        "step": 4,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Done! ✓ I've built a 7-segment counter circuit with:\n\n- **7-segment display (cathode-common)** wired to pins 2–8 via 220Ω current-limiting resistors\n- **Button on pin 9** with INPUT_PULLUP (pull LOW when pressed)\n- **Sketch logic**: reads the button, increments the counter on each press, wraps 9 → 0, and updates the display using a digit-to-segment lookup table (0–9)\n- **Debounce**: 200ms delay after each button press to avoid false triggers\n\nPress the button and the display will count up: 0, 1, 2, … 9, 0, 1, …"
      }
